&quot; Torch joined the Australian Station in February 1897, serving in New Zealand waters in 1898 and 1899.  She was part of the naval escort for the visit of the Duke and Duchess of York to Australia and New Zealand aboard the chartered Royal liner HMS Ophir during 1901.  After a refit, she recommissioned at Sydney on 29 November 1913. In July 1914 Torch, in company with the French cruiser Kersaint, was involved with a native uprising on the Island of Wala, Vanuatu. Five men were killed and four injured, and one native prisoner was captured.  In August 1914 she became part of the New Zealand Division of the Pacific Station. &quot;
